name: 2009-pulaski-county-geotiff-tiles
notes: One foot ground resolution, natural color (RGB), 8-bit digital orthophotography for Pulaski County, Arkansas. The imagery was collected using the Leica Geosystems ADS40 sensor between February 5th and March 6th, 2009 at an average altitude of 9,600 feet above ground level. The National Elevation Dataset (NED) was used as vertical control. Airborne GPS/IMU data was used as horizontal control. The imagery was produced by Pixxures, Inc. under contract for DigitalGlobe, Inc.
